4
00:00:24.072 --> 00:00:26.875
[Hannah] <i>You've heard of
the butterfly effect. right?</i>

5
00:00:28.577 --> 00:00:31.370
<i>That if a butterfly flaps its
wings at just the right time</i>

6
00:00:31.371 --> 00:00:33.006
<i>in just the right place...</i>

7
00:00:35.333 --> 00:00:38.428
<i>it can cause a hurricane
thousands of miles away.</i>

8
00:00:44.009 --> 00:00:45.226
[woman] Hold on.

9
00:00:51.975 --> 00:00:53.392
Is Justin here?

10
00:00:53.393 --> 00:00:55.978
Haven't seen him for days.
I thought he was with you.

11
00:00:55.979 --> 00:00:58.031
He told me he was going home last night.

12
00:00:58.315 --> 00:00:59.690
Yeah. well. he didn't.

13
00:00:59.691 --> 00:01:02.160
- [man] Who is it. Am?
- Justin's girlfriend.

14
00:01:03.361 --> 00:01:04.913
[sighs]

15
00:01:05.322 --> 00:01:06.581
Girlfriend. huh?

16
00:01:07.157 --> 00:01:10.418
Tell that little shit that his
mother is worried sick. all right?

17
00:01:10.952 --> 00:01:13.713
Yeah. She looks it.

18
00:01:14.748 --> 00:01:17.041
Tell him call her today or
don't bother coming home.

19
00:01:17.042 --> 00:01:20.044
<i>♪ Heads up We're in a dead club... ♪</i>

20
00:01:20.045 --> 00:01:21.763
[Hannah]<i> It's chaos theory.</i>

21
00:01:22.255 --> 00:01:26.267
<i>But. see. chaos theory
isn't exactly about chaos.</i>

22
00:01:26.843 --> 00:01:31.097
<i>It's about how a tiny change in a
big system can affect everything.</i>

23
00:01:31.098 --> 00:01:32.598
<i>♪ Doing it to death ♪</i>

24
00:01:32.599 --> 00:01:34.558
- Fuck! What the fuck?
- [laughs]

25
00:01:34.559 --> 00:01:36.560
Dude. it's time to wakey.

26
00:01:36.561 --> 00:01:38.979
I'm rolling in ten. if
you feel like school.

27
00:01:38.980 --> 00:01:40.698
Oh. shit!

28
00:01:40.899 --> 00:01:43.651
- What's with the fucking water?
- Just having some fun.

29
00:01:43.652 --> 00:01:45.453
[mocking] "I'm just having some fun."

30
00:01:46.154 --> 00:01:49.323
Justy. you know you're welcome
here all the damn time. buddy.

31
00:01:49.324 --> 00:01:51.283
but I thought you were
going home last night.

32
00:01:51.284 --> 00:01:53.160
Yeah. that guy Seth is back.

33
00:01:53.161 --> 00:01:55.496
- Meth Seth?
- Yeth.

34
00:01:55.497 --> 00:01:56.923
[both laugh]

35
00:01:57.624 --> 00:02:00.844
And that's all. right? Just Meth Seth?

36
00:02:01.128 --> 00:02:02.971
Yeah. just that asshole.

37
00:02:03.130 --> 00:02:05.172
I can't deal with him. you know that.

38
00:02:05.173 --> 00:02:07.767
'Cause your girlfriend's texting me now.

39
00:02:10.303 --> 00:02:13.472
Brother. you know that Seth or whatever.

40
00:02:13.473 --> 00:02:16.151
I got your back. always.

41
00:02:16.476 --> 00:02:17.686
Yeah. I know.

42
00:02:17.711 --> 00:02:20.604
Whatever you did. if you
even fucking did anything.

43
00:02:20.605 --> 00:02:22.115
we can take care of it.

44
00:02:23.275 --> 00:02:24.775
I mean anything.

45
00:02:24.776 --> 00:02:26.119
You know my one rule.

46
00:02:26.720 --> 00:02:27.820
Keep you clean.

47
00:02:27.821 --> 00:02:30.165
Keep me clean. All right.

48
00:02:30.699 --> 00:02:33.460
And Jessica. take
care of her. all right?

49
00:02:33.785 --> 00:02:35.086
She's your girl.

50
00:02:37.038 --> 00:02:38.164
You want some breakfast?

51
00:02:38.165 --> 00:02:41.292
Marisa the maid's here
making some Mexican shit.

52
00:02:41.293 --> 00:02:44.053
[chuckles] You know
she's Guatemalan. right?

53
00:02:44.588 --> 00:02:45.722
Sure.

54
00:02:46.173 --> 00:02:47.932
- Hungry?
- Yeah.

55
00:02:49.134 --> 00:02:52.729
[Hannah] <i>Chaos theory.</i>
<i>Sounds dramatic. but it's not.</i>

56
00:02:54.139 --> 00:02:55.607
<i>Ask a mathematician.</i>

57
00:02:56.016 --> 00:02:59.110
<i>Or better yet. ask someone
who's been in a hurricane.</i>

58
00:02:59.519 --> 00:03:01.937
<i>♪ We're double sixing it ♪</i>

59
00:03:01.938 --> 00:03:06.650
<i>♪ Night after night after night ♪</i>

60
00:03:06.651 --> 00:03:09.361
<i>♪ We're double sixing it ♪</i>

61
00:03:09.362 --> 00:03:13.750
<i>♪ Night after night after night ♪</i>

62
00:03:16.703 --> 00:03:17.837
Wanna help?

63
00:03:19.122 --> 00:03:20.581
Do I want help?

64
00:03:20.582 --> 00:03:23.968
Do you want to help? Put up posters.

65
00:03:26.755 --> 00:03:28.255
No. no thanks. Marcus.

66
00:03:28.256 --> 00:03:29.891
Come on. school spirit.

67
00:03:30.175 --> 00:03:32.343
All right? Making a contribution.

68
00:03:32.344 --> 00:03:33.561
Giving back.

69
00:03:33.970 --> 00:03:35.763
Giving back to who. exactly?

70
00:03:35.764 --> 00:03:38.066
[band warming up]

71
00:03:38.475 --> 00:03:40.351
Why are they playing in the courtyard?

72
00:03:40.352 --> 00:03:43.279
Uh. yeah. They asked student
council. Thought it was a great idea.

73
00:03:43.730 --> 00:03:45.198
Got a concert tonight.

74
00:03:46.274 --> 00:03:48.368
We got some glum chums.

75
00:03:49.361 --> 00:03:51.862
[Hannah] <i>Alex Standall.</i>
<i>You caused the hurricane.</i>

76
00:03:51.863 --> 00:03:52.997
<i>It's your turn.</i>

77
00:03:53.281 --> 00:03:54.698
F.M.L. forever.

78
00:03:54.699 --> 00:03:56.242
F.M.L. forever.

79
00:03:56.243 --> 00:03:57.743
F.M.L. forever.

80
00:03:57.744 --> 00:04:00.755
[Hannah] <i>Little did I know</i>
<i>you would F. my L. forever.</i>

81
00:04:02.082 --> 00:04:04.500
<i>Little did I know you
would be my hurricane.</i>

82
00:04:04.501 --> 00:04:05.918
- Hey. Alex.
- Hey.

83
00:04:05.919 --> 00:04:08.212
- You okay?
- Yeah. I just... I overslept.

84
00:04:08.213 --> 00:04:10.589
Mr. McLean wants us to
start with "Take Five."

85
00:04:10.590 --> 00:04:13.601
- He thinks that'll raise spirits.
- Love me some Brubeck.

86
00:04:13.885 --> 00:04:17.805
Though of course it was written
by Paul Desmond. but whatever.

87
00:04:17.806 --> 00:04:20.900
If they want a spirit-raiser.
how about "Gloomy Sunday"?

88
00:04:21.434 --> 00:04:24.654
Are you serious? That
song's totally depressing.

89
00:04:25.021 --> 00:04:27.273
Or it's beautiful. if you have taste.

90
00:04:27.274 --> 00:04:29.033
Or if you're suicidal.

91
00:04:35.240 --> 00:04:36.240
Way to go. Troy.

92
00:04:36.241 --> 00:04:37.866
Aw. shit.

93
00:04:37.867 --> 00:04:40.202
Was he friends with Hannah
Baker? I didn't know.

94
00:04:40.203 --> 00:04:42.505
[Hannah] <i>Maybe you
think I'm being silly.</i>

95
00:04:43.248 --> 00:04:46.583
<i>I'm some stupid girl who gets all
worked up over a little thing.</i>

96
00:04:46.584 --> 00:04:48.511
<i>But little things matter.</i>

97
00:04:50.422 --> 00:04:54.309
<i>For instance. you never told me
when you started dating Jessica.</i>

98
00:04:56.344 --> 00:04:58.730
<i>But I remember just how it ended.</i>

99
00:04:59.347 --> 00:05:01.149
<i>- With your list.</i>
- [sighs]

100
00:05:03.685 --> 00:05:05.695
Is "Gloomy Sunday" really a song?

101
00:05:06.646 --> 00:05:09.741
Yeah. Google "Hungarian Suicide Song."

102
00:05:10.442 --> 00:05:12.035
I'll take your word for it.

103
00:05:14.904 --> 00:05:16.039
Alex.

104
00:05:17.824 --> 00:05:19.125
Can we. um...

105
00:05:21.119 --> 00:05:22.337
talk about this?

106
00:05:25.248 --> 00:05:26.957
What is there to talk about?

107
00:05:26.958 --> 00:05:29.510
- Is Hannah telling the truth?
- What do you think?

108
00:05:29.794 --> 00:05:31.628
Did you do what she said you did?

109
00:05:31.629 --> 00:05:32.764
Did you?

110
00:05:34.090 --> 00:05:37.810
Alex. "Take the 'A'
Train." with your solo.

111
00:05:38.344 --> 00:05:39.636
All right. well.

112
00:05:39.637 --> 00:05:42.982
I guess if I'm gonna be happy.
may as well do it with the Duke.

113
00:05:44.225 --> 00:05:46.518
- [drumsticks tapping]
- [band playing mellow rock]

114
00:05:46.519 --> 00:05:49.656
[Hannah] <i>Alex. we hadn't talked</i>
<i>since you two got together.</i>

115
00:05:50.952 --> 00:05:56.174
<i>And then it seemed like maybe you
might not be together anymore.</i>

116
00:06:00.909 --> 00:06:02.960
- Hey. Jess.
- Hey.

117
00:06:03.161 --> 00:06:04.379
Mrs. Antilly?

118
00:06:04.746 --> 00:06:05.880
Yeah.

119
00:06:06.581 --> 00:06:07.799
Everything okay?

120
00:06:08.291 --> 00:06:09.583
What. like in the world?

121
00:06:09.584 --> 00:06:11.302
Or with you.

122
00:06:11.753 --> 00:06:12.970
Yeah.

123
00:06:13.171 --> 00:06:16.590
You could drop by our office later.
if you want to make a full report.

124
00:06:16.591 --> 00:06:17.966
Our office?

125
00:06:17.967 --> 00:06:19.218
Monet's.

126
00:06:19.219 --> 00:06:21.479
Oh. Yeah. right.

127
00:06:21.596 --> 00:06:23.189
I forgot about that.

128
00:06:23.515 --> 00:06:24.765
The office thing.

129
00:06:24.766 --> 00:06:26.475
Yeah. It's been a while.

130
00:06:26.476 --> 00:06:28.903
Yeah. there's just so much going on.

131
00:06:32.221 --> 00:06:33.523
Male!

132
00:06:33.548 --> 00:06:35.349
Females.

133
00:06:35.819 --> 00:06:39.163
Hey. how about a Monet's reunion today?

134
00:06:39.948 --> 00:06:43.960
You have a few drink selections
left on your great menu journey.

135
00:06:43.993 --> 00:06:45.461
You were so committed once.

136
00:06:45.995 --> 00:06:47.955
Yeah. commitment's hard for Alex.

137
00:06:47.956 --> 00:06:50.582
At least I have the ability
to try something new in life.

138
00:06:50.583 --> 00:06:52.718
[Hannah] <i>Is that why you did it. Alex?</i>

139
00:06:54.629 --> 00:06:55.805
Mrs. Baker.

140
00:06:56.756 --> 00:06:58.683
Hi. I wasn't expecting you.

141
00:06:59.259 --> 00:07:00.968
Olivia. Please.

142
00:07:00.969 --> 00:07:02.854
Yeah. Well. come on in.

143
00:07:04.180 --> 00:07:06.974
Thank you for making the time.

144
00:07:06.975 --> 00:07:08.609
I-I. uh...

145
00:07:09.018 --> 00:07:10.310
I know how busy you are.

146
00:07:10.311 --> 00:07:11.687
No. not at all.

147
00:07:11.688 --> 00:07:13.698
- [shuts door]
- What can I do for you?

148
00:07:17.193 --> 00:07:18.861
Well. I was. um.

149
00:07:18.862 --> 00:07:23.666
I'm wondering if you could tell me
something about Hannah's school life.

150
00:07:24.409 --> 00:07:26.785
I mean. was she unhappy here?

151
00:07:26.786 --> 00:07:27.920
Well...

152
00:07:28.204 --> 00:07:30.581
I don't think I can answer that.

153
00:07:30.582 --> 00:07:33.125
I know you can't possibly
know every student.

154
00:07:33.126 --> 00:07:37.680
but my husband and I. we're
still trying to understand.

155
00:07:40.175 --> 00:07:42.769
At home. Hannah was... Well. I mean...

156
00:07:43.219 --> 00:07:45.804
sometimes she would run around the house

157
00:07:45.805 --> 00:07:48.849
singing show tunes in funny
voices and showering us with hugs.

158
00:07:48.850 --> 00:07:50.860
and other times...

159
00:07:51.644 --> 00:07:56.509
she was quiet and moody and it'd
be hard to get a word out of her.

160
00:07:56.534 --> 00:08:00.129
- Sure.
- But nothing she did told us she was...

161
00:08:01.571 --> 00:08:02.788
capable of...

162
00:08:02.813 --> 00:08:06.329
I'm afraid I'm going to have to
stop you right there. Mrs. Baker.

163
00:08:06.354 --> 00:08:08.494
I'm terribly sorry for your loss.

164
00:08:08.495 --> 00:08:12.331
and I wish I could
offer you what you need.

165
00:08:12.332 --> 00:08:14.383
but I just can't.

166
00:08:16.127 --> 00:08:18.471
Now that lawyers are involved.

167
00:08:19.506 --> 00:08:20.756
What are you saying?

168
00:08:20.757 --> 00:08:23.425
What I'm saying is that.
in light of your lawsuit.

169
00:08:23.426 --> 00:08:27.021
I shouldn't even be talking to you.

170
00:08:27.430 --> 00:08:28.648
I see.

171
00:08:29.974 --> 00:08:31.266
So then why are you?

172
00:08:31.267 --> 00:08:34.186
You and your husband are
members of our school community.

173
00:08:34.187 --> 00:08:37.907
and we want nothing more than
to support you during this time.

174
00:08:40.818 --> 00:08:43.663
I can only imagine your grief.

175
00:08:44.447 --> 00:08:48.042
You can't imagine the first
thing about my life right now.

176
00:08:49.869 --> 00:08:51.578
- [sobbing]
- [door opens]

177
00:08:51.579 --> 00:08:54.248
- [girl 1] Bryce is a total vampire.
- [girl 2 chuckles]

178
00:08:54.249 --> 00:08:55.999
That thing on your neck is huge.

179
00:08:56.000 --> 00:08:57.677
Oh. I know. right?

180
00:09:00.672 --> 00:09:01.973
[exhales sharply]

181
00:09:06.219 --> 00:09:07.562
[gasping breath]

182
00:09:09.138 --> 00:09:10.982
[whimpers]

183
00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:18.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

184
00:09:22.110 --> 00:09:24.662
[Hannah] <i>Maybe you say
it's nothing. Alex.</i>

185
00:09:26.281 --> 00:09:27.582
<i>It's just words.</i>

186
00:09:41.796 --> 00:09:42.921
[sniffles]

187
00:09:42.922 --> 00:09:44.307
[camera shutter clicks]

188
00:09:49.012 --> 00:09:50.396
[camera shutter clicks]

189
00:09:51.180 --> 00:09:52.264
Seriously. Tyler?

190
00:09:52.265 --> 00:09:56.235
If you're going to do a memorial.
I'm going to take pictures.

191
00:09:57.353 --> 00:09:59.739
Mrs. Baker. Hi.

192
00:10:01.399 --> 00:10:03.117
I'm Courtney Crimsen.

193
00:10:06.821 --> 00:10:08.831
I'm so sorry for your loss.

194
00:10:09.365 --> 00:10:10.708
I hope you like it.

195
00:10:11.242 --> 00:10:12.627
People keep adding to it.

196
00:10:12.952 --> 00:10:16.255
Um. every day there's
another card or more flowers.

197
00:10:16.956 --> 00:10:20.584
All these people were Hannah's friends?

198
00:10:20.585 --> 00:10:24.013
Mm-hmm. She had so many friends and...

199
00:10:24.964 --> 00:10:27.141
we all miss her so much.

200
00:10:27.592 --> 00:10:30.978
Anyone who knew Hannah would
know that she hated roses.

201
00:10:33.806 --> 00:10:35.775
She thought they were a cliché.

202
00:10:36.142 --> 00:10:38.527
[bell rings]

203
00:10:47.445 --> 00:10:49.538
["Whatever You Want" playing]

204
00:10:50.406 --> 00:10:51.791
[Clay] Hannah.

205
00:10:52.575 --> 00:10:53.876
Hey. Hannah.

206
00:10:55.078 --> 00:10:56.462
- Hey.
- Morning. Helmet.

207
00:10:57.664 --> 00:10:58.923
Urgent question.

208
00:10:59.165 --> 00:11:02.051
Have you noticed anything
weird about Alex lately?

209
00:11:02.669 --> 00:11:06.588
Um... Well. his hair's
weird. but that's not new.

210
00:11:06.589 --> 00:11:08.465
His hair is awesome.

211
00:11:08.466 --> 00:11:11.968
I didn't say it wasn't awesome.
it's just. like. distinctive.

212
00:11:11.969 --> 00:11:13.595
And he's an amazing dresser.

213
00:11:13.596 --> 00:11:15.555
I mean. you could take a few lessons.

214
00:11:15.556 --> 00:11:16.640
I totally could.

215
00:11:16.641 --> 00:11:19.017
And I'm glad we got
around to my failings

216
00:11:19.018 --> 00:11:21.362
because I was wondering
when we would get to that.

217
00:11:22.230 --> 00:11:23.823
Are you working tonight?

218
00:11:23.981 --> 00:11:25.565
Yeah. we're both on at six.

219
00:11:25.566 --> 00:11:27.785
I mean. I think. On the schedule.

220
00:11:29.195 --> 00:11:31.947
So. speaking of tonight. I
don't know if you know this.

221
00:11:31.948 --> 00:11:34.917
but there's a penumbral
lunar eclipse at 11:49.

222
00:11:35.451 --> 00:11:36.585
A what?

223
00:11:37.620 --> 00:11:39.454
The Earth's shadow is the penumbra.

224
00:11:39.455 --> 00:11:41.456
Tonight. the moon is
gonna pass through it.

225
00:11:41.457 --> 00:11:44.626
Last show is at nine. and if we
clean fast. and we probably can.

226
00:11:44.627 --> 00:11:48.130
because no kids are coming to that
English movie because it's boring.

227
00:11:48.131 --> 00:11:53.436
we could get out in time. and I
could maybe point it out to you.

228
00:11:53.886 --> 00:11:55.020
If you want.

229
00:11:56.556 --> 00:11:58.274
You want to show me the moon?

230
00:11:59.308 --> 00:12:01.852
There would be a shadow.
Not like a full eclipse.

231
00:12:01.853 --> 00:12:03.988
You wouldn't exactly see the...

232
00:12:04.272 --> 00:12:05.406
But. yeah.

233
00:12:05.815 --> 00:12:07.065
[chuckles]

234
00:12:07.066 --> 00:12:10.327
You should. like. patent yourself.

235
00:12:11.904 --> 00:12:14.707
And. yes. I will look
at the moon with you.

236
00:12:15.491 --> 00:12:17.084
I might even howl.

237
00:12:17.493 --> 00:12:19.211
Cool. Cool.

238
00:12:19.620 --> 00:12:21.714
So. yeah. I'll see you tonight.

239
00:12:24.750 --> 00:12:25.968
[locker doom slams]

240
00:12:34.302 --> 00:12:36.437
Anyways. is Justin still missing?

241
00:12:37.096 --> 00:12:40.107
He's not missing. I
know exactly where he is.

242
00:12:43.561 --> 00:12:45.353
[sighs] So he's at Bryce's.

243
00:12:45.354 --> 00:12:46.480
Maybe you should go.

244
00:12:46.481 --> 00:12:48.565
I shouldn't have to
go. He should be here.

245
00:12:48.566 --> 00:12:51.818
Then go get him. Drag him back
to school by his perfect hair.

246
00:12:51.819 --> 00:12:53.320
Right.

247
00:12:53.321 --> 00:12:54.488
You know what?

248
00:12:54.489 --> 00:12:57.616
Tell him that you entered
him into that costume contest.

249
00:12:57.617 --> 00:12:59.117
Two hundred bucks.

250
00:12:59.118 --> 00:13:01.921
Yeah. maybe he could dress
